list.name: Default Changelist
list.comment: Fixed bug of not updatingPopulationEqualityMeasure after a move. Moved incrementing badMoves into else block of if (acceptBadMove) {} else {} Added all initialization in AlgorithmController and return MoveUpdater object from continueAlgorithm() Fixed bug in removePrecinct() where precinct was not properly being removed by GeoID Added extra check to make sure the neighbor district we move to is not from the same district Updated ajax in mapjs.js to receive the MoveUpdater object Updated deviation and penalty in algorithms.properties

task.summary: Added District.loadDefaultProperties to TestClass and state.initPopScores() method Added a run10SA method in Algorithm class (incomplete) Added initialization of Algorithm parameters in AlgorithmController class Added toString() methods to AlgorithmData, AlgorithmWeights, and Move classes Fixed ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException in Precinct class Fixed errors in State class: Fixed NullPointerException in getRandomDistrict() method Edited getPopulation() so that it calculates state population based on district populations Changed all occurrences of districts to defaultDistrict Added initPopScores() method

In Algorithm, modified run10SA() method so that it moves the largestBorderPrec of the lowestPopScoreDistrict. We are adding to the Move Stack as long as the population of the lowestPopScoreDistrict is decreasing, which means its popScore is increasing. In District, modified calculatePopEqualScore() method so a penalty has a linear relationship with deviation from idealPop. Added getLargestBorderPrec() and moveLargestBorderPrec() methods In State, added getLowestPopScoreDistrict() method Added population_deviation and population_penalty to algorithms.properties
merged and updated stateloader now all precinct have voteData
